Sound Sensor Characterization
Overview
This project evaluates the performance characteristics of a sound sensor by comparing measured sound levels with known reference sound levels. The goal was to determine:
Sensor sensitivity
Measurement accuracy
Operating range
Relationship between RMS output and sound pressure level (dB)
The sensor was tested using controlled audio signals and measurements were recorded for analysis.
Experimental Setup
Reference Conditions
Silent room baseline: ~40 dB
Calibration signal: 1 kHz tone at 70 dB
During calibration:
70 dB → RMS = 1
This calibration point was used to normalize the RMS measurements from the sensor.
RMS Response vs Sound Level
Measured relationship between sound level (dB) and sensor RMS output:
